Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.
Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add
scallion whites; cook ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup} and 3/4 cup
water. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until tender,
about ~{15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain @pineapple{4%ounce} over a #small bowl{}, reserving juice.
Roughly chop pineapple. Trim @green beans{6%ounce}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.
In a second small bowl, combine pineapple, scallion greens, lime zest (to taste),
juice from 1 lime wedge, and 2 TBSP pineapple juice. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Toss green beans on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.
Roast on top rack until browned and tender, about ~{10-12%minutes}.

Pat @barramundi{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and
pepper. Season flesh side of fish with @Southwest spice blend{1%teaspoon}; rub to
evenly coat.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add barramundi, skin side down. Cook until skin is crispy, about
~{4-5%minutes}. (TIP: Lower heat if skin begins to brown too quickly.) Flip and
cook until fish is cooked through, about ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer
to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp}, remaining lime zest (to taste),
and juice from 1 lime wedge. Season with salt and pepper. Divide rice, barramundi,
and green beans between plates. Top fish with salsa. Serve with remaining lime
wedges on the side for squeezing over.